Keep libc++ availability annotations enabled on Apple for ArcticDB back-deploy.
ArcticDB patch: keep libc++ availability annotations enabled on Apple so the
macOS wheel back-deploys correctly. Disabling them makes libc++ assume newer
system-dylib symbols (e.g. std::__hash_memory) exist and emit strong references
to them, which are absent on the deployment target and break dlopen on older
macOS. Linux libc++ has no vendor availability annotations, so keep it there.

diff --git a/CMakeLists.txt b/CMakeLists.txt
--- a/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -143,7 +143,14 @@
 
     # Allow the use of not visible yet availabile features, such
     # as some formatter for new types.
-    add_compile_definitions(_LIBCPP_DISABLE_AVAILABILITY)
 endif()
 
 # Linter options
